normal excel vs Advanced Excel:
===============================

normal excel:
=============
	formula based
	=cellname1+cellname2
	
	format: or extension: .xlsx

advanced excel:
================

	programming based
	GUI - Graphical user interface
	    - Label,Button,Textbox,Choice,List,Image,...	
	VBA - developed by microsoft

	format: .xlsm (macro enabled workbook)


excel parts:
============
	- title bar
	- menus 	(file,insert,edit,view,formula,review,help)
		(developer - menu advanced excel)
	- property 
	-namebox
	-formula bar
	-1 2 3 4 -----1048576 row header (horizontal)
	-a b c d......aa >col header( vertical)
			16384
	- sheets bar
	- status bar

shortcut keys:
==============

select cells : shift+arrowkeys
unselect cells: arrowkeys
copy : ctrl+c
paste: ctrl+v

cut : ctrl+x

full row select: shift+space
full col select: ctrl+space

col delete:
		 ctrl + -
row delete:	
		ctrl -

one sheet to another sheet: ctrl+page up/down

new sheet creation: shift+f11

full screen:alt+v+u

propety bar hide/show: ctrl+f1

vba code: alt+f11

undo or previous one: ctrl+z (backward)

redo or repeat: ctrl+y (forward)

edit cell:f2

select all:ctrl+a

row insert: ctrl+shift++
col insert: ,,

hide column:  ctrl+0
unhide column: alt+h   o u l 	or ctrl+shift+0

hide row: ctrl+9
unhide row: ctrl+shift+9

wrap text: alt+enter
formula down: ctrl+d

formulas:
==========
1)vlookup
2)hlookup
3)textfunction
  upper
  lower
  len
  left
  right
  concate
  mid
  large
  rank
  if and or not
  sum
  sumif
  count
  countif
  averge
  abs
  power
  text - number to text    ex: =text(cellname,"0.00") (left align)

  int  - text to number	   ex: =int(cellname)	(right align)
	whole number

  value- text to number	   ex: =value(cellname)	(right align)
	floating number

	











